bison34.commit_message:
YYDECL, yyterminate fixed

 - Thanks a lot to Francis Dupont for help!
OptVendorData ctor now takes const char *
Regenerated files using modern bison and flex
Migrated to variants and token constructors
Random shit sprinkled here and there
Some failed attempts to fix SrvLexer.l

SrvParser.y now generates with bison 3.4.1

 - but the generated code is total crap

fix misguided (and broken) usage of clock_gettime(CLOCK_MONOTONIC_RAW, ...)

 - Fix bugs introduced by a copy and paste mistakes (assignment to
   the wrong variable if the call to clock_gettime() succeeds in
   TAddrIA::getT2Timeout() and the addition of bogus calls to
   this->setTimestamp(ts) (ie calls which were not there in the
   original code and not related to the change from time() to
   clock_gettime()) in TAddrIA::getT1Timeout() and
   TAddrIA::getT2Timeout()

 - Replace CLOCK_MONOTONIC_RAW with CLOCK_MONOTONIC. For the purpose
   of replacing time() (ie resolution of seconds), there's no clear
   reason to use CLOCK_MONOTONIC_RAW with clock_gettime() instead of
   the more widely supported CLOCK_MONOTONIC. The incremental
   adjustments performed by adjtime() and NTP are limited to small
   changes which should not effect timers, timeouts, etc measured in
   seconds.

 - Avoid needlessly calling both time() and clock_gettime()

Signed-off-by: Andre McCurdy <armccurdy@gmail.com>
Fix to trigger client notify script whenever the expiry event occurs for addresses/prefixes assigned from remote DHCPv6 server.

Fix calling parameters for TOptIAPrefix

prefix length and validity were swapped causing wrong prefix length to
be requested (often 255) during prefix delegation in SOLICIT messages.

Signed-off-by: Matthieu Patou <mat@matws.net>

Fixed vulnerabilities with time checking.
When a system time is changed, the saved time which is calculated using system call time(),
is compared with latest time, All the addresses are timing out and we are reacquiring the address.

This will be constant even if the system time changed.

fix-subnet-calculation.commit_message: [HACK] override the timeout while waiting for more work to be 30s

Fix timeout calculation

1) use the monotonic clock everywhere (if avail) instead of mostly
   everywhere leaving a few places where it's still using the time(NULL)
   no matter what. This avoid issues when we end up comparing number of
   second since unix epoch (time(NULL)) and number of second since the
   system booted (without taking clock change)

2) Don't override ts by the value of clock for T2 timeout

Signed-off-by: Matthieu Patou <mat@matws.net>

Fix subprefix calculation

Previously prefixes like /60 would not work

Signed-off-by: Matthieu Patou <mat@matws.net>

Fix configure and makefile templates to properly detect system gtest

Fix the file searched to be libgtest.a instead of libgtests.a, only
build libgtest.a in tests/utils if we have a source gtest.
Remove the hard coded use of `$(top_builddir)/tests/utils/libgtest.a`.
Move `-pthread` in the Clnt/Srv Makefiles

Fixed vulnerabilities with time checking.
When a system time is changed, the saved time which is calculated using system call time(),
is compared with latest time, All the addresses are timing out and we are reacquiring the address.

Changed to use CLOCK_MONOTONIC_RAW, which is equivalent to hardware ticks.
This will be constant even if the system time changed.

master.commit_message:
fix misguided (and broken) usage of clock_gettime(CLOCK_MONOTONIC_RAW, ...)

 - Fix bugs introduced by a copy and paste mistakes (assignment to
   the wrong variable if the call to clock_gettime() succeeds in
   TAddrIA::getT2Timeout() and the addition of bogus calls to
   this->setTimestamp(ts) (ie calls which were not there in the
   original code and not related to the change from time() to
   clock_gettime()) in TAddrIA::getT1Timeout() and
   TAddrIA::getT2Timeout()

 - Replace CLOCK_MONOTONIC_RAW with CLOCK_MONOTONIC. For the purpose
   of replacing time() (ie resolution of seconds), there's no clear
   reason to use CLOCK_MONOTONIC_RAW with clock_gettime() instead of
   the more widely supported CLOCK_MONOTONIC. The incremental
   adjustments performed by adjtime() and NTP are limited to small
   changes which should not effect timers, timeouts, etc measured in
   seconds.

 - Avoid needlessly calling both time() and clock_gettime()

Signed-off-by: Andre McCurdy <armccurdy@gmail.com>
Fix to trigger client notify script whenever the expiry event occurs for addresses/prefixes assigned from remote DHCPv6 server.

Fix calling parameters for TOptIAPrefix

prefix length and validity were swapped causing wrong prefix length to
be requested (often 255) during prefix delegation in SOLICIT messages.
